      </div>
      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
	<p>The edition is based on <ref target="bibl:SeshadriShastri19371938">Seshadri Sastri 1937–1938</ref>. He surmised that it belonged to the reign of Vāsiṣṭhīputra Śrī Puḷumāvi (this would be necessary if the reading is indeed panatrise).</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" rend="break-none" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	    <gap reason="lost" quantity="14" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">saṃva</supplied>chare
	  <lb n="2"/>
	    pana<supplied reason="lost">trise</supplied>
	    <gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character"/>
	    <supplied reason="lost">pakhe chaṭhe</supplied>
	    6 divasa
	  <lb n="3"/>
	    prathamo 1
	    <gap reason="lost" quantity="8" unit="character"/>
	    ka-koṭubikasa
	  <lb n="4"/>
	    <persName key="pers:Skandanāga">khadanāgasa</persName>
	    a<gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/>r<unclear>i</unclear>kena 
	    <placeName key="pl:Agaloka">agalokakena</placeName>
	    <persName key="pers:Vīraskanda">virakha<supplied reason="lost">da</supplied>sa</persName>
	  <lb n="5"/>
	    putena amacena<app><note xml:lang="en"><p>This line has been
	      added after the rest of the inscription 
	      was completed.</p></note></app>
	  <lb n="6"/>
	    ataporena 
	    <placeName key="pl:Dhānyakaṭaka">dhañakaḍasa</placeName>
	    mahāvihāre puva-dāre pava<lb n="7" break="no"/>jitāna
	    bhikhu-saghasa puvasel<unclear>i</unclear>yāna nigāyasa
	  <lb n="8"/>
	    parigaha dhamacaka-dhayo paḍiṭḥapito
	    sava-loka<lb n="9" break="no"/>satya-hita-sukhāya
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  In the (35th) year ... on the first day, the minister 
	  Atapora from Agaloka, son of Vīraskanda,
	  had this dharma-cakra pillar set up at the east gate of
	  the great vihāra at 
	  <placeName key="pl:Dhānyakaṭaka">Dhānyakaṭaka</placeName>
	  for the ascetics of the monastic community, for the
	  association of the Pūrvaśailīyas, for the truth
	  and benefit and happiness of all people.
	</p>
      </div>
